userResponse.message: OLAP 分析常见的功能应用场景

result.token: - I'm looking into what OLAP means for data analysis. It's short for Online Analytical Processing, a tech that helps analyze data.
- OLAP lets you view data from multiple angles, which is great for business intelligence. It offers quick, interactive access to large datasets.

results.title: Online analytical processing - Wikipedia
results.preview: CaseOLAP – Context-aware Semantic OLAP, developed for biomedical applications. The CaseOLAP platform includes data preprocessing (e.g., downloading, extraction, and parsing text documents), indexing and searching with Elasticsearch, creating a functional document structure called Text-Cube, and quantifying user-defined phrase-category relationships using the core CaseOLAP algorithm. Unlike relational databases, which had SQL as the standard query language, and widespread APIs such as ODBC, JDBC and OLEDB, there was no such unification in the OLAP world for a long time. The first real standard API was OLE DB for OLAP specification from Microsoft which appeared in 1997 and introduced the MDX query language. Several OLAP vendors – both server and client – adopted it. In 2001 Microsoft and Hyperion announced the XML for Analysis specification, which was endorsed by most of the OLAP vendors.
results.description: Apache Doris is an open-source real-time analytical database based on MPP architecture. It can support both high-concurrency point query scenarios and high-throughput complex analysis. Apache Druid is a popular open-source distributed data store for OLAP queries that is used at scale in production by various organizations. Apache Kylin is a distributed data store for OLAP queries originally developed by eBay. Cubes (OLAP server) is another lightweight open-source toolkit implementation of OLAP functionality in the Python programming language with built-in ROLAP. ClickHouse is a fairly new column-oriented DBMS focusing on fast processing and response times. DuckDB is an in-process SQL OLAP database management system.

results.title: An Introduction to Online Analytical Processing (OLAP) - Imply
results.preview: While there are various types of OLAP databases—such as Multidimensional OLAP, Relational OLAP, and Hybrid OLAP—these products are all intended for similar goals. MOLAP databases organize data into data cubes for analysis, ROLAP databases are arranged much like SQL databases, and HOLAP combines the best of both types. As the database for speed, scale, and streaming data, Apache Druid was created as an OLAP solution that can merge the best of both worlds: the fast response times and concurrent support of transactional databases, alongside the complex operations and massive scale of analytical databases.  · Druid is also easily scaled up or down, as query, storage, and cluster coordination functions are devolved across separate node types that can be added or removed on demand. Afterwards, data and workloads are automatically rebalanced or retrieved from deep storage and redistributed throughout nodes.
results.description: Online analytical processing (OLAP) analyzes data at scale—and provides actionable insights to organizations. Learn about how OLAP works, what a data cube is, and which OLAP product to use.

results.title: What is OLAP? Online Analytical Processing Definition | AtScale
results.preview: Semantic Layer – Semantic layer applications enable the development of a logical and physical data model for use by OLAP-based business intelligence and analytics applications. The Semantic Layer ensures that the data consumed by these applications is modeled in a multidimensional form singularly (one instance), consistently and made accessible easily. Companies like AtScale also provide the capability to automate OLAP-based data query optimization via creating data aggregation tables within the data models based on query frequency and performance / response time. Business Intelligence Tools – These tools automate the OLAP queries, making it easier for data analysts and business-oriented users to create reports and analyses without having to involve IT / technical resources. ... Semantic Layer – The semantic layer is a common, consistent representation of the data used for business intelligence used for reporting and analysis, as well as for analytics.
results.description: Learn what OLAP (Online Analytical Processing) is from AtScale. Understand the definition and how it supports complex data analysis for business insights.

results.title: What is OLAP? - Online Analytical Processing Explained - AWS
results.preview: AWS databases provide various managed cloud databases to help organizations store and perform online analytical processing (OLAP) operations. Data analysts use AWS databases to build secure databases that align with their organization's requirements. Organizations migrate their business data to AWS databases because of the affordability and scalability.  · Amazon Redshift is a cloud data warehouse designed specifically for online analytical processing. Amazon Relational Database Service (Amazon RDS) is a relational database with OLAP functionality. Data engineers use Amazon RDS with Oracle OLAP to perform complex queries on dimensional cubes. Amazon Aurora is a MySQL- and PostgreSQL-compatible cloud relational database. It is optimized for running complex OLAP workloads. Get started with OLAP on AWS by creating an AWS account today. ... Instantly get access to the AWS free tier.
results.description: What is Online Analytical Processing, how and why businesses use Online Analytical Processing, and how to use Online Analytical Processing with AWS.

results.title: What is OLAP: A Complete Guide to Online Analytical Processi
results.preview: Online Analytical Processing can be defined as a set of tools and approaches to represent data from multiple dimensions. In a broader sense, it includes a bunch of practices aimed at modeling data/databases and creating specific analytical solutions. OLAP systems are capable of combining classic tables in a sort of table of tables, which can be visualized as a 3D OLAP Cube for simplicity. A typical OLAP system will include the following components that perform dedicated functions to handle analytical queries. Data source. This could be a transactional database or any other storage we take data from. The data in its standard format isn’t optimized for OLAP queries, so it requires transformation and remodeling before it can be used. OLAP database is where we store data for analysis. Usually, transformation takes place before the data is uploaded to a database, but the approach may vary.
results.description: A concise guide to OLAP databases, cubes, differentiation between OLAP and OLTP. Data modeling and business intelligence architecture in terms of OLAP.

results.title: Online Analytical Processing - Azure Architecture Center | Microsoft Learn
results.preview: SQL Server Analysis Services provides OLAP and data-mining functionality for business intelligence applications. You can either install SQL Server Analysis Services on local servers or host it within a virtual machine (VM) in Azure. Analysis Services is a fully managed service that provides the same major features as SQL Server Analysis Services. Analysis Services supports connecting to various data sources in the cloud and on-premises in your organization. Clustered columnstore indexes are available in SQL Server 2014 and higher and in SQL Database. These indexes are ideal for OLAP workloads. Beginning with SQL Server 2016, including SQL Database, you can take advantage of hybrid transactional and analytical processing (HTAP) through updateable nonclustered columnstore indexes. Use HTAP to perform OLTP and OLAP processing on the same platform. This approach eliminates the need for multiple copies of your data and separate OLTP and OLAP systems.
results.description: Learn about online analytical processing solutions to organize large databases and support complex analysis without affecting transactional systems.

results.title: What is OLAP? | IBM
results.preview: Learn more about OLAP, a core component of data warehousing implementations to enable fast, flexible data analysis.
results.description: OLAP tools are designed for multidimensional analysis of data in a data warehouse, which contains both transactional and historical data. In fact, an OLAP server is typically the middle, analytical tier of a data warehousing solution. Common uses of OLAP include data mining and other business intelligence applications, complex analytical calculations, and predictive scenarios, as well as business reporting functions like financial analysis, budgeting, and forecast planning. OLTP is designed to support transaction-oriented applications by processing recent transactions as quickly and accurately as possible. Common uses of OLTP include ATMs, e-commerce software, credit card payment processing, online bookings, reservation systems, and record-keeping tools. For a deep dive into the differences between these approaches, check out "OLAP vs. OLTP: What's the Difference?"

results.title: Overview of Online Analytical Processing (OLAP) - Microsoft Support
results.preview: Retrieving OLAP data You can connect to OLAP data sources just as you do to other external data sources. You can work with databases that are created with Microsoft SQL Server OLAP Services version 7.0, Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services version 2000, and Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services version 2005, the Microsoft OLAP server products. Excel can also work with third-party OLAP products that are compatible with OLE-DB for OLAP. You can display OLAP data only as a PivotTable report or PivotChart report or in a worksheet function converted from a PivotTable report, but not as an external data range. You can save OLAP PivotTable reports and PivotChart reports in report templates, and you can create Office Data Connection (ODC) files (.odc) to connect to OLAP databases for OLAP queries. When you open an ODC file, Excel displays a blank PivotTable report, which is ready for you to lay out.

results.title: What Is OLAP? (With Operations, Uses, Benefits and Types) | Indeed.com
results.preview: Depending on the type of analysis businesses need, they may choose to use one or more of these business intelligence models. Here are the main types of OLAP systems: This is the original and most commonly used OLAP. MOLAP can be the fastest and easiest way to process and analyze data, as it stores data in multidimensional arrays and usually processes data before a user accesses it. Often, data cubes contain every answer to possible queries, like what sales were in a given location during a specific month, providing quick responses to user queries. Precomputation, or the ability to process data without a user querying the program, is one of the major benefits of MOLAP. Here are a few other reasons to use this type: ... ROLAP is multidimensional but organizes data in relational tables where the system doesn’t precompute data. When using operations like slicing, ROLAP creates scenarios based on the data.
results.description: Learn what online analytical processing (OLAP) is, discover its operations and uses, learn what its benefits are and explore three types of OLAP systems.

modelResponse.message:
### 关键要点
- OLAP 分析在商业智能、财务分析、销售与市场分析等领域有广泛应用。
- 研究表明，它还用于供应链管理、人力资源分析、医疗研究、零售和电信行业。
- 证据倾向于支持 OLAP 在能源、农业和基础设施可观测性中的新兴应用。
- 这些场景因行业而异，可能涉及复杂的数据处理和多维度分析。

#### 商业智能与报告
OLAP 分析帮助企业生成报告和仪表板，分析销售数据、财务表现和市场趋势。它似乎特别适合需要快速洞察的场景。

#### 财务与预算分析
在财务领域，OLAP 用于预算编制、预测和财务报告，允许从不同角度（如部门或产品）分析数据。

#### 销售与市场分析
OLAP 帮助销售和市场团队分析销售数据、客户人口统计和活动表现，优化营销策略和销售预测。

#### 其他应用场景
OLAP 还应用于供应链管理、医疗研究、零售、电信、能源、农业和基础设施可观测性等领域，具体取决于行业需求。

---

### 详细报告

以下是关于 OLAP（在线分析处理）分析常见功能应用场景的全面探讨，涵盖了各种行业和业务功能。这些场景基于对多个可靠来源的分析，确保提供全面和最新的信息。

#### 背景与定义
OLAP 是一种技术，允许用户从多个视角分析数据，通常用于商业智能，帮助用户快速交互地访问数据并查询大量数据。它特别适合处理多维度数据，常见于数据仓库解决方案的分析层。

#### 常见功能应用场景
以下是 OLAP 分析的主要应用场景，按行业和功能分类：

- **商业智能与报告**  
  OLAP 被广泛用于生成报告、仪表板和可视化，帮助企业理解销售数据、财务表现、市场趋势和客户行为。例如，它可以分析特定时间段内的销售表现或客户购买模式。

- **财务分析与预算**  
  在财务领域，OLAP 用于预算编制、预测和财务报告。财务专业人员可以从部门、产品或时间维度分析数据，例如评估季度预算表现或预测未来收入。

- **销售与市场分析**  
  OLAP 帮助销售和市场团队分析销售数据、客户人口统计和活动表现。这可以优化目标定位、改进营销策略并提高销售预测。例如，分析某产品在不同地区的销售表现。

- **供应链与库存管理**  
  OLAP 用于分析供应链数据，如库存水平、供应商表现和物流成本，帮助企业优化运营并降低成本。例如，分析库存周转率以减少过剩库存。

- **人力资源与劳动力分析**  
  OLAP 应用于 HR 数据，分析员工表现、离职率和培训需求，支持数据驱动的劳动力管理决策。例如，评估不同部门的员工满意度。

- **医疗与医学研究**  
  在医疗行业，OLAP 用于分析患者数据、治疗结果和医学研究数据，改善患者护理并支持研究。例如，分析特定疾病的治疗效果。

- **零售与电子商务**  
  OLAP 在零售和电子商务中至关重要，用于分析销售数据、客户行为和库存水平，优化定价、产品摆放和库存管理。例如，分析高峰购物季的销售趋势。

- **电信**  
  OLAP 用于分析通话数据记录、客户使用模式和网络性能，改善服务质量和客户满意度。例如，分析网络拥堵时间以优化资源分配。

- **能源与公用事业**  
  OLAP 分析客户消费数据以确定模式、预测未来使用量，并为电网改进或能源投标提供信息。例如，分析用电模式以优化能源分配。

- **农业**  
  作为新兴应用，OLAP 用于分析作物产量、土壤条件和天气模式，支持更有效的农业实践。例如，分析降雨量对作物生长的影响。

- **可观测性**  
  在数字基础设施中，OLAP 用于维护、改进和故障排除系统，通过分析大量数据确保系统性能。例如，分析服务器日志以识别性能瓶颈。

- **业务流程管理 (BPM)**  
  OLAP 应用于业务流程管理，分析和优化业务流程。例如，分析订单处理时间以改进运营效率。

#### 行业与功能的交叉分析
以下表格总结了 OLAP 在不同行业中的典型应用场景：

| **行业**            | **典型应用场景**                          |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------|
| 商业智能            | 销售报告、财务仪表板、市场趋势分析        |
| 财务                | 预算编制、收入预测、财务报告              |
| 销售与市场          | 客户行为分析、活动表现、销售预测          |
| 供应链              | 库存管理、供应商表现、物流成本分析        |
| 人力资源            | 员工表现、离职率、培训需求分析            |
| 医疗                | 患者数据分析、治疗结果、医学研究          |
| 零售与电子商务      | 销售趋势、客户行为、库存优化              |
| 电信                | 网络性能、客户使用模式、服务质量          |
| 能源与公用事业      | 消费模式分析、预测使用量、电网改进        |
| 农业                | 作物产量、土壤条件、天气模式分析          |
| 基础设施            | 系统性能、故障排除、日志分析              |
| 业务流程管理        | 订单处理时间、运营效率优化                |

#### 数据来源与可靠性
这些场景基于对多个来源的分析，包括维基百科、Imply、AtScale 和 AWS 等，提供技术定义和实际应用案例。信息截至 2025 年 6 月 25 日，确保与当前时间一致。

#### 局限性与未来趋势
虽然 OLAP 在上述场景中表现出色，但其复杂性可能需要技术专长。未来趋势包括语义层、自动化和自助服务分析的增强，可能进一步扩展其应用范围。

webSearchResults.title: Online analytical processing - Wikipedia
webSearchResults.preview: CaseOLAP – Context-aware Semantic OLAP, developed for biomedical applications. The CaseOLAP platform includes data preprocessing (e.g., downloading, extraction, and parsing text documents), indexing and searching with Elasticsearch, creating a functional document structure called Text-Cube, and quantifying user-defined phrase-category relationships using the core CaseOLAP algorithm. Unlike relational databases, which had SQL as the standard query language, and widespread APIs such as ODBC, JDBC and OLEDB, there was no such unification in the OLAP world for a long time. The first real standard API was OLE DB for OLAP specification from Microsoft which appeared in 1997 and introduced the MDX query language. Several OLAP vendors – both server and client – adopted it. In 2001 Microsoft and Hyperion announced the XML for Analysis specification, which was endorsed by most of the OLAP vendors.
webSearchResults.description: Apache Doris is an open-source real-time analytical database based on MPP architecture. It can support both high-concurrency point query scenarios and high-throughput complex analysis. Apache Druid is a popular open-source distributed data store for OLAP queries that is used at scale in production by various organizations. Apache Kylin is a distributed data store for OLAP queries originally developed by eBay. Cubes (OLAP server) is another lightweight open-source toolkit implementation of OLAP functionality in the Python programming language with built-in ROLAP. ClickHouse is a fairly new column-oriented DBMS focusing on fast processing and response times. DuckDB is an in-process SQL OLAP database management system.

Afterwards, data and workloads are automatically rebalanced or retrieved from deep storage and redistributed throughout nodes.

webSearchResults.title: What is OLAP: A Complete Guide to Online Analytical Processi
webSearchResults.preview: Online Analytical Processing can be defined as a set of tools and approaches to represent data from multiple dimensions. In a broader sense, it includes a bunch of practices aimed at modeling data/databases and creating specific analytical solutions. OLAP systems are capable of combining classic tables in a sort of table of tables, which can be visualized as a 3D OLAP Cube for simplicity. A typical OLAP system will include the following components that perform dedicated functions to handle analytical queries. Data source. This could be a transactional database or any other storage we take data from. The data in its standard format isn’t optimized for OLAP queries, so it requires transformation and remodeling before it can be used. OLAP database is where we store data for analysis. Usually, transformation takes place before the data is uploaded to a database, but the approach may vary.

webSearchResults.title: Online Analytical Processing - Azure Architecture Center | Microsoft Learn
webSearchResults.preview: SQL Server Analysis Services provides OLAP and data-mining functionality for business intelligence applications. You can either install SQL Server Analysis Services on local servers or host it within a virtual machine (VM) in Azure. Analysis Services is a fully managed service that provides the same major features as SQL Server Analysis Services. Analysis Services supports connecting to various data sources in the cloud and on-premises in your organization. Clustered columnstore indexes are available in SQL Server 2014 and higher and in SQL Database. These indexes are ideal for OLAP workloads. webSearchResults.preview: Learn more about OLAP, a core component of data warehousing implementations to enable fast, flexible data analysis.
webSearchResults.description: OLAP tools are designed for multidimensional analysis of data in a data warehouse, which contains both transactional and historical data. In fact, an OLAP server is typically the middle, analytical tier of a data warehousing solution. Common uses of OLAP include data mining and other business intelligence applications, complex analytical calculations, and predictive scenarios, as well as business reporting functions like financial analysis, budgeting, and forecast planning. OLTP is designed to support transaction-oriented applications by processing recent transactions as quickly and accurately as possible. Common uses of OLTP include ATMs, e-commerce software, credit card payment processing, online bookings, reservation systems, and record-keeping tools. Cubes (OLAP server) is another lightweight open-source toolkit implementation of OLAP functionality in the Python programming language with built-in ROLAP. citedWebSearchResults.preview: While there are various types of OLAP databases—such as Multidimensional OLAP, Relational OLAP, and Hybrid OLAP—these products are all intended for similar goals. MOLAP databases organize data into data cubes for analysis, ROLAP databases are arranged much like SQL databases, and HOLAP combines the best of both types. As the database for speed, scale, and streaming data, Apache Druid was created as an OLAP solution that can merge the best of both worlds: the fast response times and concurrent support of transactional databases, alongside the complex operations and massive scale of analytical databases.  · Druid is also easily scaled up or down, as query, storage, and cluster coordination functions are devolved across separate node types that can be added or removed on demand. Afterwards, data and workloads are automatically rebalanced or retrieved from deep storage and redistributed throughout nodes.

citedWebSearchResults.title: What is OLAP: A Complete Guide to Online Analytical Processi
citedWebSearchResults.preview: Online Analytical Processing can be defined as a set of tools and approaches to represent data from multiple dimensions. In a broader sense, it includes a bunch of practices aimed at modeling data/databases and creating specific analytical solutions. OLAP systems are capable of combining classic tables in a sort of table of tables, which can be visualized as a 3D OLAP Cube for simplicity. A typical OLAP system will include the following components that perform dedicated functions to handle analytical queries. Data source. This could be a transactional database or any other storage we take data from. The data in its standard format isn’t optimized for OLAP queries, so it requires transformation and remodeling before it can be used. OLAP database is where we store data for analysis. Usually, transformation takes place before the data is uploaded to a database, but the approach may vary.

citedWebSearchResults.title: Online Analytical Processing - Azure Architecture Center | Microsoft Learn
citedWebSearchResults.preview: SQL Server Analysis Services provides OLAP and data-mining functionality for business intelligence applications. You can either install SQL Server Analysis Services on local servers or host it within a virtual machine (VM) in Azure. Analysis Services is a fully managed service that provides the same major features as SQL Server Analysis Services. Analysis Services supports connecting to various data sources in the cloud and on-premises in your organization. Clustered columnstore indexes are available in SQL Server 2014 and higher and in SQL Database. These indexes are ideal for OLAP workloads. Beginning with SQL Server 2016, including SQL Database, you can take advantage of hybrid transactional and analytical processing (HTAP) through updateable nonclustered columnstore indexes. Use HTAP to perform OLTP and OLAP processing on the same platform. This approach eliminates the need for multiple copies of your data and separate OLTP and OLAP systems.

citedWebSearchResults.title: What is OLAP? | IBM
citedWebSearchResults.preview: Learn more about OLAP, a core component of data warehousing implementations to enable fast, flexible data analysis.
citedWebSearchResults.description: OLAP tools are designed for multidimensional analysis of data in a data warehouse, which contains both transactional and historical data. In fact, an OLAP server is typically the middle, analytical tier of a data warehousing solution. Common uses of OLAP include data mining and other business intelligence applications, complex analytical calculations, and predictive scenarios, as well as business reporting functions like financial analysis, budgeting, and forecast planning. OLTP is designed to support transaction-oriented applications by processing recent transactions as quickly and accurately as possible. Common uses of OLTP include ATMs, e-commerce software, credit card payment processing, online bookings, reservation systems, and record-keeping tools. For a deep dive into the differences between these approaches, check out "OLAP vs. OLTP: What's the Difference?"

Here are the main types of OLAP systems: This is the original and most commonly used OLAP. MOLAP can be the fastest and easiest way to process and analyze data, as it stores data in multidimensional arrays and usually processes data before a user accesses it. Often, data cubes contain every answer to possible queries, like what sales were in a given location during a specific month, providing quick responses to user queries. Precomputation, or the ability to process data without a user querying the program, is one of the major benefits of MOLAP. Here are a few other reasons to use this type: ...
